            <term xml:id="term-k000109-8" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin-nt">tongwa</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000109-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant">筒瓦</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000109-3" xml:lang="zh-Hant">㼧瓦</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000109-4" xml:lang="zh-Hans">筒瓦</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000109-6" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin">tǒngwǎ</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000109-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">t'ong-wa</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000109-7" xml:lang="en" type="literal_translation" source="#biblk000109-1">barrel tiles (lit.)</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000109-1" xml:lang="en" type="ATTCAT_preferred">barrel tiles (ATTCAT preferred)</term>
       <note type="Note">
               <p xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000109-2">Barrel tiles. A type of ceramic roofing tile with a semi-circular (or greater) cross section. Usually used as a covering tile to prevent water from seeping between two rows of concave/gutter tiles (<term ref="/keyword/kooo104">banwa 瓪瓦</term>). Also written 㼧 (tong (lit. convex tile)).</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant">瓦的一種，也寫作“㼧瓦”。通常是半圓形（或大半圓形），用於屋面作為蓋瓦。</p>
	    </note>
            <note type="related concepts">
               <p xml:id="related-concept-k000109-1" xml:lang="zh-Hant" >瓦 wǎ</p>
               <p xml:id="related-concept-k000109-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant" ref="/keyword/k000110">瓦當 wǎdàng</p>
               <p xml:id="related-concept-k000109-3" xml:lang="zh-Hant" >㼧瓦 tóngwǎ</p>
            </note>
